ygData.subject: RE: [EQ_women] Digest Number 166
ygData.msgSnippet: I m in Anarchy Online now and was in the beta.  Yes you really can do stuff in an hour.  But - grouping probably isn t it, solo missions are great for that
ygData.messageBody:
I'm in Anarchy Online now and was in the beta.  Yes you really can do stuff in an hour.  But - grouping probably isn't it, solo missions are great for that time frame.  You also lose "chat" in solo missions at level 6 - and it makes for a very lonely time after (high player turnover rate now too).
 
I do like it though.   I'm mainly on first dimension now since the second is sooo empty during the day when I play.  Let me know who you are I'll send you a tell ;0  And if you describe your playstyle I can give you a list of classes to fit.
 
Lora / Hechicera on boards

Wow, I loved Brell.  If my characters havent' been axed I still have some there.
 
I promised my son when he turned 13 he could play EQ so he set up his account last night.  He has a friend on Xev so I'll reactivate my acct. to play with him (gotta stay in the loop with my teen).  But I WILL NOT GET READDICTED!  Actually, my life is very full now and I don't think I have time to get readdicted.  It's what I'll do when I have custody (yeah, well... that's another story) and we want to play together.
 
Trying Anarchy Online too, as long as I'm at it - see what it's like.  I hear you can actually have a productive play session in only an hour so it may work out better for me.
 
Gonna try enchanter... Luna, HELP! 
 
Ice
